ZH: 我们家里的醋是自己做的。
EN: The vinegar in our house is homemade.

ZH: 这个菜需要加一点点醋来调味。
EN: This dish needs a little vinegar for seasoning.

ZH: 姥姥做的饺子里加了一勺醋。
EN: Grandma added a spoonful of vinegar to the dumplings.

ZH: 这种沙拉酱里面有醋的味道。
EN: This kind of salad dressing has a taste of vinegar.

ZH: 美食家们都知道醋是烹饪的必备品。
EN: Foodies all know that vinegar is a must-have for cooking.

ZH: 醋的种类有很多种，不同的用途。
EN: There are many types of vinegar for different purposes.

ZH: 它们是用葡萄汁，苹果圆或米酿制成的。
EN: They are made from grape juice, apple cider, or rice wine.

ZH: 醋可以增加食物的酸味。
EN: Vinegar can enhance the sourness of food.

ZH: 一些人喜欢在凉拌菜里加入一点醋。
EN: Some people like to add a little vinegar to cold dishes.

ZH: 醋还可以用来去除一些食物的腥味。
EN: Vinegar can also be used to remove the fishy smell of some foods.

ZH: 醋所含的酸性成分可以促进食物的消化。
EN: The acidic components in vinegar can promote digestion of food.

ZH: 孕妇最好少食用含有醋的食物。
EN: Pregnant women are advised to consume less vinegar-containing food.

ZH: 做糖醋排骨要用到一些醋。
EN: Making sweet and sour ribs requires some vinegar.

ZH: 醋可以去除瓷器上的水垢。
EN: Vinegar can remove water stains on porcelain.

ZH: 经常食用酸类食物和醋，对哮喘病人不太好。
EN: Eating sour foods and vinegar regularly may not be good for asthma patients.

ZH: 这个药方里面还加了点醋。
EN: This prescription also contains a little vinegar.

ZH: 在炖肉时，醋可以让肉更容易变烂。
EN: When stewing meat, vinegar can soften the meat more easily.

ZH: 在中国烹饪中，最常用到的是米醋和陈醋。
EN: In Chinese cuisine, the most commonly used vinegars are rice vinegar and aged vinegar.

ZH: 醋的使用方法要根据具体情况来决定。
EN: The use of vinegar should be determined based on specific circumstances.

ZH: 在一些特定的食物上，撒一点醋就能提升它们的口感。
EN: Sprinkling a little vinegar on some specific foods can enhance their taste.
